cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about spoken language understanding (SLU) in task-oriented dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a Context Encoding Language Transformer (CELT) model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses transfer learning approaches, which can be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
